Plain English Summary (Optional)
Today I learned how to impersonate one service account using another 
by creating a delegation chain. I generated short lived tokens for workload-sa using the 
IAM Credentials API and verified access to allowed and 
forbidden buckets. I added a time based IAM Condition to restrict access to 
the allowed bucket for only one hour. I removed the unconditional
binding so the condition would be enforced. I confirmed that IAM Conditions 
work as expected: access is granted within the window and denied outside. I also learned 
that Cloud Storage IAM does not support IP based conditions, so IP 
restrictions must be handled elsewhere (VPC SC, Cloud Armor).

